Who We Are

A Vision for Tomorrow's Uganda

The Youth Liberation Club (YLC) is a non-political brainchild of a group of students aimed at establishing a socially and morally sound Ugandan youth through youth-to-youth interactions for a positive influence.

We started because we noticed something: many of us who once shared the same bright dreams have taken different, often darker paths. Drug abuse, criminality, school dropouts â€” these are not just individual failures. They are a warning signal for our nation's future.

Since youth are influenced most by their peers, YLC chooses to be that influence â€” steering fellow youth toward purpose, integrity, and a revived future, with the help of The Almighty God.

Club Objectives

01

To create a socially moral youth community in Uganda based on the values of integrity and authenticity.

02

To encourage the youth in Uganda to embrace and take part in the education activity â€” whether in or outside Uganda.
